race.comment: DARN DEADLY (11) travels from Kembla Grange for her resumption. He's right up to this and owns a Kembla trial win. Well placed to win. ZALE (5) went forward and proved too strong over 1200m at Bathurst first up in a CL1. Has an awkward gate but is further improved. He's capable of going back-to-back. WRITTEN BY LUCY (10) is a leader and assess his chances on the lip defeat at Nowra two back over this distance. He will get every chance from an inside barrier and has each-way claims. MAN FROM BRUSSELLS (4) was a comfortable winner here this grade over 1000m heavily bet. The longer sprint is a niggle but he has the inside gate and 3x winning rider Cahill stays aboard. In the mix.
